      "message": "Have a couple of questions here.\n\n1. A sensor going out of range does not mean the power supply is no longer operational.\n2. How are you getting this on IPMI?  Generally this is a discrete sensor, which as far as I know there is no support for.\n\n\nOverall, I\u0027m not sure we want this.  If a power supply wants to use the sensor itself to mark itself non-operational, that\u0027s fine.  But if the power supply has determined that is it still operational, by setting the bit in pmbus, why would we override it in the BMC?",
